description: Iaxartes/Silis/Tanais fl. (Syr Darya river) is a river of Central Asia. It flows from the Tian Shan Mountains in Kyrgyzstan and eastern Uzbekistan to the remains of the Aral Sea.
details: The Barrington Atlas Directory notes: Syr Darya Burushaski: ts.hil, ‘water’
